race.comment: SANTO SOSPIR (18) represents notable connections. The four-year-old made a winning debut on heavy ground here in February before a decent return effort last month finishing 9L fourth in a 3200m maiden hurdle at Wexford. Progress likely. Leading contender. SOUND AS A BELL (19) caught the eye during April winning a 4800m point-to-point in style. Racing for top owners and rates a likely player. READY FOR ROAD (17) shaped well on debut producing a decent fourth contesting a 3200m maiden hurdle at Cork three weeks back. Open to improvement up in trip. L'AS DE WATT (11) out performed odds on the same fixture at Cork when 5L second tackling 3200m. Next best.
